Since $g(x)=2x^2-2x-3$, we have  \begin{align*}
g(3)&=2(3)^2 - 2(3) - 3\\
&=2(9)-6-3\\
&=18-9\\
&=\boxed{9}.
\end{align*} Therefore, we have $f(g(3))=f(9)$. Since $f(x)=2\sqrt{x} + \frac{12}{\sqrt{x}}$, this is equal to \begin{align*}
f(9)&=2\sqrt{9}+\frac{12}{\sqrt{9}} \\
&=2(3)+\frac{12}{3}\\
&=6+4\\
&= \boxed{10}.
\end{align*}
